### CTYPE.H FUNCTIONS

Character Classification
isalnum(): Checks for an alphanumeric character (letter or digit).
isalpha(): Checks for an alphabetic character (letter).
isblank(): Checks for a blank space or tab character.
iscntrl(): Checks for a control character (e.g., newline, backspace).
isdigit(): Checks for a decimal digit (0-9).
isgraph(): Checks for a printable character, excluding the space character.
islower(): Checks for a lowercase letter.
isprint(): Checks for a printable character (including space).
ispunct(): Checks for a punctuation character (printable, but not alphanumeric or space).
isspace(): Checks for any whitespace character.
isupper(): Checks for an uppercase letter.
isxdigit(): Checks for a hexadecimal digit (0-9, a-f, A-F). 

Character Transformation
tolower(): Converts an uppercase letter to its lowercase equivalent.
toupper(): Converts a lowercase letter to its uppercase equivalent. 


